# Ignore .claude tool state and local settings; track shared review infrastructure.
# The inner .claude/.gitignore (managed by oh-my-claudecode) re-includes agents/,
# conventions/, skills/, and output-styles/ — the root intentionally overrides those
# so tool-specific dirs remain private and only project-defined files are tracked.
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/commands/**
!.claude/pr-rules/
!.claude/pr-rules/**
